									<p><strong>Chartered Tourism Manager (CTM)®</strong> is an advanced-level certification designed for professionals aiming to excel in the global hospitality and tourism industries. To ensure participants have a solid foundation, CTM® requires either completion of the <strong>American Certified Tourism Professional (ACTP)®</strong> credential (or an equivalent foundational certification in tourism management), <strong>or</strong> a minimum of <strong>six years of relevant industry experience.</strong> This prerequisite guarantees that all candidates enter the CTM® program with a robust understanding of essential tourism principles and practices, paving the way for in-depth exploration of strategic leadership, global operations, and innovative practices in the dynamic world of hospitality and tourism sectors. From overseeing five-star hotels and airport operations to optimizing cruise line schedules and destination marketing strategies, CTM® equips you with the strategic insight, managerial skills, and innovative mindset required to excel in a dynamic, interconnected global market.</p>								</div>
